</div><br>
<b>Parkview Rhine Garden Pre-school and Parkview-Rhine Garden International Nursery</b> were established in 1994. The Rhine Garden School encompasses two campuses, situated on the podium of Rhine Garden, Sham Tseng, within Tower One and Tower Five. In September 2007, Parkview Rhine Garden Pre-School became a non-profit institution, enabling parents to benefit from subsidies provided under the 'Kindergarten Education Scheme' administered by the Education Bureau (EDB). Conversely, Parkview-Rhine Garden International Nursery, continues to operate as a private independent school, where the 'Kindergarten Education Scheme' from the EDB does not apply.<br><br>
  </div>

  <div class="col-lg-5 pt-4">
  	<a href="https://www.facebook.com/PIPSRG/" target="_blank"><img src="/images/icon_facebook.jpg"></a>
	<span style="margin-left: 18px"></span>
	<a href="https://www.instagram.com/pipsrhinegarden/" target="_blank"><img src="/images/icon_ig.jpg"></a>

	<br><br>

